{
  "text": "Chemokines exert their effect by binding to their membrane receptors, the expression of which may modulate their action. Two specific receptors for IL-8 have been identified on the surface of human neutrophils. The type A (CXCR1) binds with high affinity only to IL-8, but binds neutrophilactivating peptide-2 (NAP-2) and granulocyte-related oncogene-a (GROa) with low affinity. The type B (CXCR2) receptor binds the above three chemokines with high affinity (Ray and [CITATION_1] .",
